    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin allows you to replace an attachment file by uploading another image or by downloading one from a specified URL, without deleting the attachment. The plugin handles the image sizes generation and the attachment metadata update, and you will see the result right away.</p>\n<h4>Demo</h4>\n<p><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"750\" height=\"422\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/7kGf8cz49ZE?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></p>\n<h3>License</h3>\n<p>This program is distributed in the hope that it will be useful, but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.</p>\n",
        "faq": "<p>None</p>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>3.4.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added <code>avif</code> to the allowed file types list</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>3.4.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up to 6.6</li>\n<li>Exposed the sub-sizes in the replace view</li>\n<li>Added the link to replace view in the attachment details modal available in the Media Library in grid mode</li>\n<li>Additional changes related to forcing the image cache cleanup after replacement</li>\n<li>Accessibility enhancement for the replace view</li>\n<li>Additional changes that attempt to create missing folders and files on the server to fix attachments that have only database references</li>\n<li>Styles updates for compatibility with core changes</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See the <a href=\"changelog.txt\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">changelog</a> for detailed information on changes made in the earlier versions.</p>\n"
    },
    "short_description": "Replace easily an attachment file by uploading another file or by downloading one from an URL, without deleting the attachment.",
